commit.message:
pipenv version clash workaround

Should close issues #18 / #21 with the least
bad workaround. I consider it unlikely that
many people using black and flake8-black would
be using anything older than black 19.3b0 which
is now over a year old.
Minor version bump for testing under flake8 v3.8

Remove failing relative path test case

This test case seemed to work prior to flake8 v3.8,
after which paths are now resolved relative to CWD
making this test case futile:

https://gitlab.com/pycqa/flake8/-/merge_requests/363

See my issue #13.

Use alternative parse_options signature.

Flake8 has two choices here, first it tries
parse_options(optmanager, options, extra_args)
and if that fails with a TypeError, does
parse_options(options)

If parse_options fails, we get a cleaner single
exception if we use the first form - easier for
debugging.
